  "text": "Proximate and ultimate analyses based on standard methods [CITATION_1] were carried out for all samples, by the certified To determine the representativeness of the results, especially for SRM, which is a heterogeneous material, proximate analysis was also performed using a thermal gravimetric analyzer (TGA). The experiment, as shown in Fig. 1 , involves heating of 20 mg of samples under an inert atmosphere of Argon, at a heating rate of 10°C/min from room temperature to 110°C, the samples were kept at this temperature for 10 min to remove residual moisture. Afterward, the samples were heated up to 950°C still under an inert atmosphere of Argon; the weight loss observed in this stage is associated with volatile content. Finally, the sample was kept at a temperature of 950°C for 5 h, while the atmosphere was changed from Argon to air. Since this stage involves oxidation of carbon, the weight loss observed is associated with the fixed carbon content of material, and remaining material represents ash [CITATION_2] . The experiment was repeated five times, for determining the reproducibility of results.",
